article.headline: Jacksonville 64, North Florida 60
article.story: strdflo JACKSONVILLE, Fla. (AP) -- Jesse Kimbrough scored 11 of his 16 points in the second half to lead visiting Jacksonville to a 64-60 win over cross-town rival North Florida Tuesday. Jacksonville (7-8, 3-2 Atlantic Sun Conference) got a 3-point basket from freshman Ben Smith to open the game and never trailed. Kimbrough started slow, hitting just two of five shots in the first half but came alive in the final 20 minutes with three baskets including a key 3-point shot and four consecutive free throws. Jacksonville held a 31-26 halftime lead and stretched the lead to 13 at 45-32 in the opening eight minutes of the second half. North Florida (2-13, 0-5) battled back midway in the half led by Aaron Caruthers who scored 11 consecutive points at one point as the Ospreys cut the lead to one at 52-51 with just more than five minutes remaining. It was still a one-point game with two minutes left when Kimbrough connected on a long 3-point shot just before the shot clock expired to give Jacksonville a 57-53 lead. The Dolphins maintained a four-point lead the rest of the game. Caruthers led North Florida with a season-high 20 points.
